race.comment: SNITZ SONIC (8) ran well on debut narrowly beaten over 1400m at Sandown-Hillside in a tougher race. Promising type with improvement to come. He sets a decent standard. TAAJWAR (9) stepped out over 1400m at Ballarat on debut beaten 1.7L. He's still a work in progress but presents fitter and maps for a soft run. A chance with the race experience on board. LOVE KAYE (10) debuts for the Laurie yard and has had four jumpouts. Moloney stays aboard from the latest and the filly jumps from the inside barrier. Profiles well and the betting will be key. MAKHANDA (3) resumed beaten 2.7L over 1500m at Bendigo. Strips fitter and deserves each-way consideration.
